Title: Sugar kettle plaque
Abstract (Description): Photograph of the English language plaque which stands next to the sugar kettle used by Jean Étienne de Boré on the LSU campus. The plaque reads: "Sugar kettle used by Jean Étienne de Boré in 1795 to granulate sugar from Louisiana cane for the first time, thus revolutionizing Louisiana's economy. The kettle was later bought by planter John Hill and given to Louisiana State University. Erected by the Louisiana Tourist Commission, 1970."
